lenders.name: Ruth and Nila
lenders.loan_because: we want to give back to other Filipinas/Filipinos, as well as those in other countries, who are struggling to overcome the negative economic/other effects of colonialism, poor governance, etc.  Education is so important, especially for girls in staying out of forced prostitution, and by helping these families to earn a decent income, we hope that it will be easier for their children to stay in school, go to college, and break the cycle of poverty--maybe even work in government or international organizations one day, and change the way the world operates so that third world nations are no longer exploited or forced to be in a state of poverty.
lenders.occupational_info: We are a mother-daughter duo.  I attend university and am studying sociology and international affairs.  I one day hope to have enough money to travel to my mother's homeland of the Philippines, and later other destinations, to volunteer my time, focussing on working with girls and women.  Mom has a degree from the Philippines and once worked there in textile manufacturing, but after emigrating to Canada in the 80's, can no longer use her degree. She now works as a store clerk.
